[[File:UENO-oji Monument.JPG|thumb|上宮之址碑]] '''上野王子'''（うえのおうじ）は、[[九十九王子]]の4番目。現在消滅。[[大阪市]][[天王寺区]]上之宮町4にある上之宮台ハイツの入り口軒下に「上宮跡」の石碑があり、ここが跡地とされているが、確証は無い。現在は、[[大江神社 (大阪市)|大江神社]]（大阪市天王寺区夕陽丘町5-40）に合祀されている。 昔、[[四天王寺]]を守る「[[四天王寺七宮|四天王寺七社]]」の上之宮[[神社]]として、鎮座していた。近くに[[上宮高等学校|上宮高校]]がある。
*最寄駅 **大江神社:[[大阪市営地下鉄谷町線]][[四天王寺前夕陽ヶ丘駅]]か[[西日本旅客鉄道|JR]][[天王寺駅]] **石碑：[[近畿日本鉄道|近鉄]][[近鉄大阪線|大阪線]][[大阪上本町駅]]
== 関連項目 == * [[熊野信仰]] * [[熊野古道]] - [[紀伊路]] * [[九十九王子]] : [[郡戸王子]] - '''上野王子''' - [[阿倍王子神社|安倍野王子]] {{神道 横}} {{DEFAULTSORT:うえのおうし}} [[Category:大阪市の神社]] [[Category:四天王寺]] [[Category:九十九王子]] [[Category:天王寺区の歴史]] [[Category:天王寺区の建築物]] {{shinto-stub}} {{Buddhism-stub}}

''{{PAGENAME}}'' is one of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|fr|Kujūkuōji|ja|九十九王子|lt=99 ōji Shrines}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]]. <!--PAGENAME magic word should be substituted in the future when this is moved to its final pagename. This was added to a few pages not created on Feb 8 because they were very barren and this gives context to the fact that they are in a large group of pages all to be translated more or less as a group similar to the Ise Shrines--> ==Overview== {{Cite sources|date=January 2025}} [[File:UENO-oji Monument.JPG|thumb|Stone monument marking the site of Ueno Ōji]] '''Ueno Ōji''' (うえのおうじ) was the fourth shrine in the {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子}} pilgrimage network. The shrine no longer exists.
A stone monument labeled "Site of the Upper Shrine" (上宮跡) stands under the eaves at the entrance of Uenomiyadai Heights, located in Uenomiyachō 4, {{ill|Tennoji-ku, Osaka|ja|天王寺区}}, {{ill|Osaka City|ja|大阪市}}. This is believed to be the shrine's former location, though there is no conclusive evidence. Currently, Ueno Ōji is enshrined within {{ill|Oe Shrine (Osaka)|ja|大江神社}} (5-40 Yūhigaokachō, Tennoji-ku, Osaka).
In the past, it was part of the "Seven Shrines of {{ill|Shitenno-ji|ja|四天王寺}}" (四天王寺七社), serving as Uenomiyachō Shrine to protect Shitenno-ji. Nearby is {{ill|Uenomiya High School|ja|上宮高等学校}}.
== Nearest Stations == * **Oe Shrine**: {{ill|Tanimachi Line|ja|Osaka Metro谷町線}} – {{ill|Shitennoji-mae Yuhigaoka Station|ja|四天王寺前夕陽ヶ丘駅}} or {{ill|JR West|ja|西日本旅客鉄道}} – {{ill|Tennoji Station|ja|天王寺駅}} * **Stone Monument**: {{ill|Kintetsu Railway|ja|近畿日本鉄道}} – {{ill|Osaka Uehommachi Station|ja|大阪上本町駅}}
== See Also == * {{ill|Kumano Faith|ja|熊野信仰}} * {{ill|Kumano Kodo|ja|熊野古道}} – {{ill|Kiiji Route|ja|紀伊路}} * {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子}} : {{ill|Kōto Ōji|ja|郡戸王子}} – '''Ueno Ōji''' – {{ill|Abeno Ōji Shrine|ja|阿倍王子神社}}
