{{Cite sources|date=January 2025}} [[File:UENO-oji Monument.JPG|thumb|Stone monument marking the site of Ueno Ōji]] '''Ueno Ōji''' (うえのおうじ) was the fourth shrine in the {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji}} pilgrimage network. The shrine no longer exists.
A stone monument labeled "Site of the Upper Shrine" (上宮跡) stands under the eaves at the entrance of Uenomiyadai Heights, located in Uenomiyachō 4, {{ill|Tennoji-ku, Osaka|ja|天王寺区}}, {{ill|Osaka City|ja|大阪市}}. This is believed to be the shrine's former location, though there is no conclusive evidence. Currently, Ueno Ōji is enshrined within {{ill|Oe Shrine (Osaka)|ja|大江神社}} (5-40 Yūhigaokachō, Tennoji-ku, Osaka).
In the past, it was part of the "Seven Shrines of {{ill|Shitenno-ji|ja|四天王寺}}" (四天王寺七社), serving as Uenomiyachō Shrine to protect Shitenno-ji. Nearby is {{ill|Uenomiya High School|ja|上宮高等学校}}.
== Nearest Stations == * '''Oe Shrine''': {{ill|Tanimachi Line|ja|Osaka Metro谷町線}} – {{ill|Shitennoji-mae Yuhigaoka Station|ja|四天王寺前夕陽ヶ丘駅}} or {{ill|JR West|ja|西日本旅客鉄道}} – {{ill|Tennoji Station|ja|天王寺駅}} * '''Stone Monument''': {{ill|Kintetsu Railway|ja|近畿日本鉄道}} – {{ill|Osaka Uehommachi Station|ja|大阪上本町駅}}== See Also == * {{ill|Kumano Faith|ja|熊野信仰}} * {{ill|Kumano Kodo|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō}} – {{ill|Kiiji Route|ja|紀伊路|1=Kiiji}} * {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji}} : {{ill|Kōto Ōji|ja|郡戸王子}} – '''Ueno Ōji''' – {{ill|Abeno Ōji Shrine|ja|阿倍王子神社}}
