{{Unreferenced|date=January 2025}} [[File:UENO-oji Monument.JPG|thumb|Stone monument marking the site of Ueno Ōji]] '''Ueno Ōji''' (うえのおうじ) was the fourth shrine in the {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|qq=}} pilgrimage network. The shrine no longer exists.
A stone monument labeled "Site of the Upper Shrine" (上宮跡) stands under the eaves at the entrance of Uenomiyadai Heights, located in Uenomiyachō 4, {{ill|Tennoji-ku, Osaka|ja|天王寺区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tennoji-ku, Osaka|qq=}}, {{ill|Osaka City|ja|大阪市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka City|qq=}}. This is believed to be the shrine's former location, though there is no conclusive evidence. Currently, Ueno Ōji is enshrined within {{ill|Oe Shrine (Osaka)|ja|大江神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oe Shrine (Osaka)|qq=}} (5-40 Yūhigaokachō, Tennoji-ku, Osaka).
In the past, it was part of the "Seven Shrines of {{ill|Shitenno-ji|ja|四天王寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shitenno-ji|qq=}}" (四天王寺七社), serving as Uenomiyachō Shrine to protect Shitenno-ji. Nearby is {{ill|Uenomiya High School|ja|上宮高等学校|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uenomiya High School|qq=}}.
== Nearest Stations == * '''Oe Shrine''': {{ill|Tanimachi Line|ja|Osaka Metro谷町線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanimachi Line|qq=}} – {{ill|Shitennoji-mae Yuhigaoka Station|ja|四天王寺前夕陽ヶ丘駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shitennoji-mae Yuhigaoka Station|qq=}} or {{ill|JR West|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/JR West|qq=}} – {{ill|Tennoji Station|ja|天王寺駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tennoji Station|qq=}} * '''Stone Monument''': {{ill|Kintetsu Railway|ja|近畿日本鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kintetsu Railway|qq=}} – {{ill|Osaka Uehommachi Station|ja|大阪上本町駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka Uehommachi Station|qq=}} == See Also == * {{ill|Kumano Faith|ja|熊野信仰|1=Kumano Three Shrines|lt=Kumano faith|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Faith|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Three Shrines|qq=}} * {{ill|Kumano Kodo|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kodo|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kodō|qq=}} – {{ill|Kiiji Route|ja|紀伊路|1=Kiiji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kiiji Route|13=User:Immanuelle/Kiiji|qq=}} * {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|qq=}} : {{ill|Kōto Ōji|ja|郡戸王子|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōto Ōji|qq=}} – '''Ueno Ōji''' – {{ill|Abe Ōji Shrine|ja|阿倍王子神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Abe Ōji Shrine|qq=}}
